- Critical bug fix for Editing

BOO! Do you love Halloween Stickers? We do! We’ve added a howlin’ good pack of spooky stickers to dress up your photos.

HP is still battling the Gremlins and have been winning the war against their pesky buggy ways.

PRINT TO SPROCKET FROM ANY APP! – Snapchat, Moments, PicCollage, you name it! To use this feature, you must turn on the sprocket share application. First tap the share icon in your photo app then swipe to the right and tap more. Finally, turn on “Print to sprocket” to enable it. *PS you can also move it to the top of your share application list by dragging the option to the top.

With Valentine’s Day coming up, you can be sure that sprocket has your back - we have all the tools for printing with love! You might have noticed that new stickers and frames arrived through the magic of the Internetz. Our technical team has worked to make that automagically possible! We also have a new Help & How To topic to help you get the best prints. Take a gander to milk all the power out of your sprocket prints! Here is the big one…we have made the Print Queue awesome and entirely non-sucky. You can now see every print and when it is coming up in the line. You can now delete individual photos or move photos to the top of the list. It’s fantastic and we think you will squeal with joy too.

No, you’re not in the Upside Down—we really do have an amazing new addition to the sprocket family…Introducing Sprocket Studio: bringing awesome 4x6 photo memories to your living room, along with in-app photo collages, greeting card templates, and a custom Photo ID capability. And if gorgeous prints aren’t enough, check out the incredible battery and bag accessories, perfect for your next trip to Hawkins. We’ve channelled our inner Eleven and battled the Demogorgon to bring you unbelievable new updates, including new collage layouts for all printers, faster Reveal performance, and Reveal How-To & Help.  Your existing sprocket is better than ever—print and share with your friends!  As always, connect with us like Dustin over CB radio (Take Survey) and share your thoughts.  Chill in the fun that only the 80’s can deliver!!!  #teamsprocket

With this update, the Reveal feature will be removed from the HP Sprocket app. You will no longer be able to scan printed photos to see related content or scan the top of your device, if you have an HP Sprocket 200, HP Sprocket Studio, or HP Sprocket Select.
